  } else {
    ensureTyped(t, n);
  }
} else {
  report(t, n, NOT_A_CONSTRUCTOR);
  ensureTyped(t, n);
}
```

But wait, `type.isFunctionType()` returns true for any function type, including those with @constructor. So the condition becomes more permissive. That should fix the bug.

Alternatively, we could change `type.isConstructor()` to `type.isFunctionType()` and keep the rest same. That is minimal.

Thus, the fixed code is:

```
private void visitNew(NodeTraversal t, Node n) {
    Node constructor = n.getFirstChild();
    JSType type = getJSType(constructor).restrictByNotNullOrUndefined();
    if (type.isFunctionType() || type.isEmptyType() || type.isUnknownType()) {
      FunctionType fnType = type.toMaybeFunctionType();
      if (fnType != null) {
        visitParameterList(t, n, fnType);
        ensureTyped(t, n, fnType.getInstanceType());
      } else {
        ensureTyped(t, n);
      }
    } else {
      report(t, n, NOT_A_CONSTRUCTOR);
      ensureTyped(t, n);
    }
}
```

